repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
Partial fix for #6613 (I still think there might be at least one case where the USED macros aren't appropriate in coroutine, but I haven't investigated in great detail yet).

Essentially what I'm worried about in this PR is:
* We access the shared ABI types through `CGLOBAL` for whatever Cython module gets imported first.
* The lifetime of those types can be longer than any individual Cython module (because they're shared) but the shared ABI types have no ref-counting linking them back to the module they rely on for their type checks.

Therefore, instead access to the shared types (from within the shared ABI code) goes through the shared module, which has its own module state struct.

Also fixes some data races related to initializing the shared types (if multiple cython modules are being imported from different threads).
